A Lagos-based businessman, Alhaji Aminu Yaro has donated N25 million to victims of the Nguru Market fire incident. The donation was announced by Governor Mai Mala Buni at the Palace of the Emir of Nguru, Mustapha Ibn Kyari and the traders at Nguru during a sympathy visitÂ  to the Emir and the traders at Nguru yesterday.   Hoodlums bath four with acid in Yola     Abducted ex-Customs chief freed in Kwara     Family, landlords parley over court judgment   Governor Buni described the fire incident as an unfortunate incident and called on the traders to take it as an act from God that is destined to happen. The governor informed the traders that his government, through the State Emergency Management Agency, will get a full assessment of the damage and come to the aid of the victims.